WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.160 --> 00:00:08.160
[classical music playing]

2
00:00:13.240 --> 00:00:14.960
[laughing]

3
00:00:15.040 --> 00:00:17.240
Pool table right here. Home cinema.

4
00:00:17.320 --> 00:00:19.800
Ah. the Harley. Shh! Best of all…

5
00:00:20.880 --> 00:00:22.000
No fuckin' way.

6
00:00:22.080 --> 00:00:25.000
Hey. if you go off the track.
it bounces around like crazy.

7
00:00:25.080 --> 00:00:27.000
It'll give you a neck
like Fernando Alonso's.

8
00:00:27.080 --> 00:00:30.200
Hey. now you can race in here instead
of being stupid on the streets. Hmm?

9
00:00:30.280 --> 00:00:32.720
-[Pedro chuckles]
-Try it. man. You'll love it.

10
00:00:33.360 --> 00:00:35.760
-[grunts]
-Yeah. see. it's hard to get in.

11
00:00:35.840 --> 00:00:37.880
-Like the real ones.
-Jesus. dude. what the hell?

12
00:00:37.960 --> 00:00:40.640
Here it is.
"Anarchy in romantic relationships."

13
00:00:40.720 --> 00:00:43.120
"It's the practice
of establishing relationships

14
00:00:43.200 --> 00:00:45.840
that aren't subject
to preexisting categories

15
00:00:45.920 --> 00:00:49.280
that have been dictated
by hegemonic social norms."

16
00:00:49.360 --> 00:00:52.840
"It implies the possibility
of maintaining multiple non-hierarchical

17
00:00:52.920 --> 00:00:54.160
sexual-affective bonds.

18
00:00:54.240 --> 00:00:56.080
given that relationships
aren't differentiated

19
00:00:56.160 --> 00:00:58.720
from one another by labels." [whistles]

20
00:00:58.800 --> 00:01:01.440
-And you actually agreed to all that?
-I didn't know what it was.

21
00:01:01.520 --> 00:01:03.680
First. a closed relationship.
then an open one.

22
00:01:03.760 --> 00:01:06.440
And now you're not even a couple.
Your thing doesn't even have a name.

23
00:01:06.520 --> 00:01:09.240
-[laughing]
-Which son of a bitch is fucking her now?

24
00:01:09.320 --> 00:01:10.920
Uh. you sure there's only one?

25
00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:13.200
I mean. "anarchy" sounds
like there'd be more than one.

26
00:01:13.280 --> 00:01:16.480
Time to face it. buddy.
Luz likes men. men plural.

27
00:01:16.560 --> 00:01:18.160
-All right!
-[Pedro grunting]

28
00:01:18.240 --> 00:01:20.520
Everybody get out of my house.
You've seen it now.

29
00:01:20.600 --> 00:01:22.880
I think your problem with Luz
is that nothing's binding you.

30
00:01:22.960 --> 00:01:24.920
You've got no children.
no mortgage. nothing.

31
00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:27.000
-Yeah. yeah. yeah. Let's go. Hey.
-Raúl. please.

32
00:01:27.080 --> 00:01:29.080
Look who's talking.
He couldn't get rid of Blanca.

33
00:01:29.160 --> 00:01:31.040
-Sure. whatever you say.
-Why don't we play pool?

34
00:01:31.120 --> 00:01:33.120
No more games. Here. give me that bottle.

35
00:01:33.200 --> 00:01:35.120
-[Santi] What an asshole.
-Hand over the bottle.

36
00:01:35.200 --> 00:01:36.840
-Go. get lost.
-Raúl. don't do your usual.

37
00:01:36.920 --> 00:01:39.000
-Go on.
-Don't smother her. Don't pursue her.

38
00:01:39.080 --> 00:01:41.440
Just don't be you. Don't screw this up!

39
00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:45.240
[line rings]

40
00:01:45.960 --> 00:01:47.920
-Luz.
-[Luz] What is it. honey?

41
00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:49.280
What are you up to?

42
00:01:50.200 --> 00:01:53.200
ALPHA MALES

43
00:01:57.360 --> 00:01:59.760
Luis. come see
what your daughter did to her hair!

44
00:01:59.840 --> 00:02:00.840
Son.

45
00:02:00.920 --> 00:02:02.640
Wait. what? Honey. no.

46
00:02:02.720 --> 00:02:04.440
You looked so beautiful with long hair.

47
00:02:04.520 --> 00:02:05.440
Handsome.

48
00:02:05.520 --> 00:02:07.160
We gotta fix this before she goes.

49
00:02:07.240 --> 00:02:09.360
But. honey.
what's so wrong with being a girl?

50
00:02:09.440 --> 00:02:10.840
I don't wanna get titties.

51
00:02:10.920 --> 00:02:13.360
Okay. but genes are so unpredictable.

52
00:02:13.440 --> 00:02:15.240
You might not be as voluptuous
as your mom.

53
00:02:15.320 --> 00:02:17.160
-Uh. Luis.
-[Luis] I'm trying to reassure her.

54
00:02:17.240 --> 00:02:19.640
[Iris] And ballet's for idiots.
I'd rather play soccer.

55
00:02:19.720 --> 00:02:21.440
[Esther] Honey. they've won the World Cup.

56
00:02:21.520 --> 00:02:22.720
Girls play soccer too.

57
00:02:22.800 --> 00:02:24.640
Yeah. but the boys' team makes more money.

58
00:02:24.720 --> 00:02:26.840
-That's true.
-[Iris] And they get to go out.

59
00:02:26.920 --> 00:02:29.280
You always let Ulises go out
with his friends.

60
00:02:29.360 --> 00:02:31.720
-Okay. but he's older than you.
-But I'm more mature.

61
00:02:31.800 --> 00:02:35.320
Uh. Iris. there are advantages
to being a girl. hon.

62
00:02:35.400 --> 00:02:36.280
Like what?

63
00:02:36.360 --> 00:02:37.680
Well… [sighs]

64
00:02:37.760 --> 00:02:39.440
Well. you can get to be pregnant.

65
00:02:39.520 --> 00:02:41.400
Is that an advantage? Mm.

66
00:02:41.480 --> 00:02:44.440
You can get into nightclubs for free.
I guess that's objectification.

67
00:02:44.520 --> 00:02:45.880
But I've never gotten in for free.

68
00:02:45.960 --> 00:02:48.520
And girls get to wear makeup.
Well. boys can too.

69
00:02:48.600 --> 00:02:50.520
And getting your period does suck. Mm-hmm.

70
00:02:50.600 --> 00:02:53.440
Uh. honey. hang on.
Come talk to me for a minute.

71
00:02:56.280 --> 00:02:58.920
This is way over our heads.
I think we should see a psychologist.

72
00:02:59.000 --> 00:03:01.520
-Fuck! There always has to be something.
-Yeah. well…

73
00:03:01.600 --> 00:03:03.640
[doorbell rings]

74
00:03:05.880 --> 00:03:07.200
Marga just kicked me out.

75
00:03:08.040 --> 00:03:09.000
Luis!

76
00:03:09.080 --> 00:03:10.960
[man on TV] Thank you so much.

77
00:03:11.040 --> 00:03:14.280
[man 2] It's pretty cozy. isn't it?
At this price. it's a steal.

78
00:03:16.320 --> 00:03:18.840
[man] I'd like to pay the deposit in cash…

79
00:03:18.920 --> 00:03:22.040
Mom. Hey. Mom. Mom.

80
00:03:22.120 --> 00:03:24.640
Enough already. okay?
You're being ridiculous.

81
00:03:24.720 --> 00:03:26.480
Please. get that man out of here.

82
00:03:26.560 --> 00:03:29.080
Hey. hey. listen to me.
Why don't we discuss this?

83
00:03:29.160 --> 00:03:31.760
No. I'm finally free.
Luz has opened my eyes.

84
00:03:31.840 --> 00:03:33.120
Luz? Which Luz?

85
00:03:33.200 --> 00:03:34.160
My lawyer.

86
00:03:34.240 --> 00:03:35.400
But why is she involved?

87
00:03:35.480 --> 00:03:37.720
Hey. don't listen to her.
She's a troublemaker.

88
00:03:38.360 --> 00:03:40.520
I'm going to Istanbul
to see the Hagia Sophia.

89
00:03:40.600 --> 00:03:43.360
See what? You gotta get back together
with your husband.

90
00:03:44.200 --> 00:03:46.480
Okay. I'll take him back right now

91
00:03:46.560 --> 00:03:49.360
if he can tell me
one thing he likes about me.

92
00:03:51.640 --> 00:03:54.000
You're very good at cooking lentils.

93
00:03:54.640 --> 00:03:55.480
What?

94
00:03:55.560 --> 00:03:58.080
Fifty years of marriage.
and that's the only thing you can say?

95
00:03:58.160 --> 00:04:00.120
[Luis mutters]

96
00:04:00.200 --> 00:04:04.280
Uh. and you're great
at remembering which pills I have to take.

97
00:04:05.040 --> 00:04:07.000
-[Luis] Say something you like about her.
-[groans]

98
00:04:07.080 --> 00:04:08.000
About her personality.

99
00:04:08.080 --> 00:04:10.480
What do you mean?
Taking care of me doesn't count?

100
00:04:12.440 --> 00:04:14.200
[sighs]

101
00:04:14.280 --> 00:04:15.880
A NETFLIX SERIES

102
00:04:15.960 --> 00:04:17.760
[classical music playing]

103
00:04:17.840 --> 00:04:19.200
ALPHA MALES

104
00:04:19.280 --> 00:04:22.360
[man] What does it mean to be a man?
It's becoming less clear.

105
00:04:22.440 --> 00:04:23.840
Is it a privilege to be a man?

106
00:04:23.920 --> 00:04:25.840
Or are we victims of masculinity?

107
00:04:25.920 --> 00:04:27.840
No one is gonna
deconstruct my masculinity.

108
00:04:27.920 --> 00:04:30.040
-[sighs] You're neo-archaic.
-What is that?

109
00:04:30.120 --> 00:04:34.480
[man] From now on. you're all
sexist pigs under deconstruction.

110
00:04:35.800 --> 00:04:37.080
[audience applauding]

111
00:04:40.560 --> 00:04:41.640
Whoo-hoo!

112
00:04:41.720 --> 00:04:42.880
Alpha Males.

113
00:04:42.960 --> 00:04:46.200
a comedy that'll make you laugh.
but will also make you think.

114
00:04:46.280 --> 00:04:47.480
We're halfway through shooting.

115
00:04:47.560 --> 00:04:49.880
and we can't wait for you
to see the finished product.

116
00:04:49.960 --> 00:04:51.600
Does anyone have any questions?

117
00:04:52.120 --> 00:04:54.200
[laughs] Don't be shy.

118
00:04:54.280 --> 00:04:56.560
-That's why we're here.
-[woman] Thank you.

119
00:04:57.760 --> 00:04:59.840
Because Bad Bitch was such a flop.

120
00:04:59.920 --> 00:05:02.600
do you feel you're fighting
to save your career with this project?

121
00:05:02.680 --> 00:05:04.560
Well. I wouldn't say that.

122
00:05:04.640 --> 00:05:07.520
This'll be a hit.
It's about real-world issues.

123
00:05:07.600 --> 00:05:10.200
What man doesn't feel like
he's a little lost these days?

124
00:05:10.280 --> 00:05:12.840
[woman 2] To be honest.
I'm already bored by the title.

125
00:05:12.920 --> 00:05:15.200
Is a feminist struggle
something to laugh at?

126
00:05:15.280 --> 00:05:16.280
[Pedro] On the contrary.

127
00:05:16.360 --> 00:05:18.880
The series is intended
to be a criticism of sexist men

128
00:05:18.960 --> 00:05:20.520
who won't adapt to modern times.

129
00:05:20.600 --> 00:05:22.040
Okay. but it seems like. in the end.

130
00:05:22.120 --> 00:05:25.280
straight white men always end up
taking up all the screen time.

131
00:05:26.960 --> 00:05:30.120
You should know
one guy's hetero-curious. [clicks tongue]

132
00:05:30.200 --> 00:05:32.640
-How'd it go with the press?
-Great.

133
00:05:32.720 --> 00:05:34.160
Very good.

134
00:05:35.360 --> 00:05:37.920
It's stirring up some controversy.
but I think that'll help us.

135
00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:39.920
That sounds great. Sit down.

136
00:05:41.800 --> 00:05:45.720
Listen. we've hired
a woman to replace you as CEO.

137
00:05:49.760 --> 00:05:50.600
Ah.

138
00:05:52.480 --> 00:05:56.640
Well. as the CEO.
that would have been good to know.

139
00:05:56.720 --> 00:05:59.800
We want you to focus
on what you're good at. being creative.

140
00:06:00.320 --> 00:06:01.720
You've got to understand that we had

141
00:06:01.800 --> 00:06:04.040
to address the negative atmosphere
in the company.

142
00:06:05.080 --> 00:06:08.200
Negative atmosphere?
Uh. I don't think I've ever noticed that.

143
00:06:08.280 --> 00:06:11.280
Pedro. women comprise 80%
of our workforce.

144
00:06:11.360 --> 00:06:13.880
[chuckles] Well. wouldn't it be good
to balance that out a little?

145
00:06:13.960 --> 00:06:16.120
Do you realize no one here speaks to you?

146
00:06:17.440 --> 00:06:19.160
No. I didn't. [clears throat]

147
00:06:21.080 --> 00:06:23.920
I find this all rather humiliating.

148
00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:26.560
but I imagine you know what's best.
It's your company.

149
00:06:26.640 --> 00:06:28.600
[José Ángel]
Virginia is in her office now.

150
00:06:28.680 --> 00:06:30.680
If you would like to go meet her.

151
00:06:31.960 --> 00:06:32.840
[knock on door]

152
00:06:32.920 --> 00:06:34.040
Come on in.

153
00:06:36.280 --> 00:06:37.120
Virginia.

154
00:06:37.640 --> 00:06:39.240
How are you. Pedro?

155
00:06:39.320 --> 00:06:41.080
Surprised. but okay.

156
00:06:41.160 --> 00:06:43.680
My schedule's tight
since we're still shooting.

157
00:06:44.200 --> 00:06:45.480
So let's grab lunch--

158
00:06:45.560 --> 00:06:48.400
I would prefer to keep our interactions
within the workplace. Hmm?

159
00:06:49.480 --> 00:06:50.880
-Sure.
-[cell phone chimes]

160
00:06:50.960 --> 00:06:54.240
I've already got the production plan
and the cost report.

161
00:06:54.320 --> 00:06:56.960
So if I have any questions.
I'll let you know.

162
00:06:57.040 --> 00:06:59.200
BRING ME CHURROS AND CHOCOLATE. PLEASE!

163
00:06:59.280 --> 00:07:01.560
-Is that important?
-No. Yes. it's my girl… my…

164
00:07:01.640 --> 00:07:03.840
[sighs] My partner is pregnant.

165
00:07:04.400 --> 00:07:07.200
-That's wonderful.
-[chuckles] Thanks. We're thrilled.

166
00:07:07.280 --> 00:07:09.320
But today. she isn't feeling so great.

167
00:07:09.400 --> 00:07:12.160
So if you're all right with it.
I'll be going now.

168
00:07:14.400 --> 00:07:15.320
If you must.

169
00:07:17.280 --> 00:07:19.600
That answer felt ambiguous.
Don't you think?

170
00:07:19.680 --> 00:07:21.440
If you have to go. you can leave.

171
00:07:23.600 --> 00:07:25.080
Oh. and one more thing.

172
00:07:25.160 --> 00:07:26.720
I am a happily married woman.

173
00:07:26.800 --> 00:07:29.200
and I never sleep
with my coworkers. by the way.

174
00:07:29.840 --> 00:07:30.760
For your peace of mind.

175
00:07:30.840 --> 00:07:32.000
[mutters]

176
00:07:33.720 --> 00:07:34.600
Oh. shit.

177
00:07:39.040 --> 00:07:40.480
[doorbell rings]

178
00:07:41.800 --> 00:07:44.040
I want you to meet Rita.
She's our new rescue dog.

179
00:07:44.120 --> 00:07:45.000
What?

180
00:07:45.080 --> 00:07:48.240
Remember you said that you
didn't have time to look after a dog?

181
00:07:48.320 --> 00:07:50.120
Yeah. and I still don't.

182
00:07:50.200 --> 00:07:52.080
[Raúl] Exactly.
and that's where I come in.

183
00:07:52.160 --> 00:07:54.320
We'll both take care of her.
We can do this together.

184
00:07:55.000 --> 00:07:56.720
Raúl. that was just an excuse.

185
00:07:56.800 --> 00:07:58.000
When I was little. I had a dog.

186
00:07:58.080 --> 00:08:00.240
and I was devastated
when we had to put it down.

187
00:08:00.320 --> 00:08:02.720
But look at this adorable little face.

188
00:08:02.800 --> 00:08:04.880
Stop emotionally blackmailing me.

189
00:08:04.960 --> 00:08:07.200
All right. all right.
I'll take her back to the shelter.

190
00:08:07.280 --> 00:08:10.400
But you do know.
that when they don't get adopted.

191
00:08:10.480 --> 00:08:12.040
then it's goodbye. Rita.

192
00:08:12.520 --> 00:08:14.120
You can be such an asshole.

193
00:08:14.200 --> 00:08:17.160
You wanna take her for a walk?
I already bought some poop bags.

194
00:08:17.240 --> 00:08:18.800
Wow. what an amazing father!

195
00:08:18.880 --> 00:08:19.800
Hey.

196
00:08:20.760 --> 00:08:23.600
How about we go stay
in the countryside this weekend?

197
00:08:23.680 --> 00:08:25.080
So she can run around in nature.

198
00:08:25.160 --> 00:08:27.560
She's been caged for so long.
the poor thing.

199
00:08:27.640 --> 00:08:29.520
Unless you have plans with that dude.

200
00:08:29.600 --> 00:08:31.320
You plotted this all out. huh?

201
00:08:31.840 --> 00:08:33.040
Every detail.

202
00:08:34.240 --> 00:08:35.880
Okay. but what
do we do about our daughter?

203
00:08:35.960 --> 00:08:39.080
Ignore it until she gets over it?
Take her to therapy? Uh…

204
00:08:39.160 --> 00:08:43.080
That's not my area.
Iris should see a pediatric psychologist.

205
00:08:43.160 --> 00:08:45.320
Okay. but as her parents.
can you tell us what to do?

206
00:08:45.400 --> 00:08:47.720
I'm here solely to help you as a couple.

207
00:08:47.800 --> 00:08:49.960
Right. but the fact
we're parents affects us as well.

208
00:08:50.040 --> 00:08:52.120
She already said it's not her area.

209
00:08:52.200 --> 00:08:54.800
I appreciate people
who don't interfere where they shouldn't.

210
00:08:54.880 --> 00:08:57.160
Okay. but if Luz doesn't do it.
another lawyer will.

211
00:08:57.240 --> 00:08:58.800
Right. she pretends to be a feminist.

212
00:08:58.880 --> 00:09:01.280
But she's actually a tight-ass
who profits off housewives.

213
00:09:01.360 --> 00:09:04.360
I'm sorry. um.
I think I need some context here.

214
00:09:04.440 --> 00:09:07.200
Well. it turns out my wife's best friend
is helping my mother

215
00:09:07.280 --> 00:09:09.800
divorce my father
after 50 years of marriage.

216
00:09:09.880 --> 00:09:12.000
She's just-- [sobbing]

217
00:09:14.840 --> 00:09:15.840
Are you crying now?

218
00:09:15.920 --> 00:09:18.880
Yeah. so what?
That's what we pay for. [sniffles]

219
00:09:18.960 --> 00:09:21.920
-[Rosa] You're bothered that he's crying?
-It's a little weird. Hmm.

220
00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:24.480
A separation often
generates feelings of impotence.

221
00:09:24.560 --> 00:09:26.440
fear and anger towards one's parents.

222
00:09:26.520 --> 00:09:28.760
Yes. I'm feeling all that.
I'm going through all that.

223
00:09:28.840 --> 00:09:32.520
[Rosa] It teaches us that. as a couple.
we should never take anything for granted.

224
00:09:32.600 --> 00:09:34.840
-[Luis] Mm-hmm.
-No matter how long you've been together.

225
00:09:34.920 --> 00:09:37.200
You have to do the work constantly.

226
00:09:37.280 --> 00:09:39.560
See? Constantly.

227
00:09:42.680 --> 00:09:44.440
[Daniela groans]

228
00:09:45.160 --> 00:09:46.600
I wanna die.

229
00:09:46.680 --> 00:09:48.800
I swear now my life has no meaning at all.

230
00:09:48.880 --> 00:09:51.080
You've posted it on Insta.
It's too late for an abortion.

231
00:09:51.160 --> 00:09:52.000
No. that's the thing.

232
00:09:52.080 --> 00:09:55.720
In the time since I posted I'm pregnant.
I've lost 2.000 follow-- [gags]

233
00:09:55.800 --> 00:09:57.840
Of course.
your target audience has shifted.

234
00:09:57.920 --> 00:09:59.840
From guys who wanted
to see you doing yoga.

235
00:09:59.920 --> 00:10:02.880
to moms who wanna show solidarity
while you're going through the shit.

236
00:10:02.960 --> 00:10:04.760
[Daniela] But I refuse to play that game.

237
00:10:04.840 --> 00:10:07.440
Sis. if you actually wanna be
a content creator at your age.

238
00:10:07.520 --> 00:10:09.360
you gotta have kids. It is what it is.

239
00:10:10.360 --> 00:10:14.480
Look. I'm ready to delete my accounts
and tell everyone to fuck off.

240
00:10:14.560 --> 00:10:17.280
Right. so you wanna be a jobless mom
who's dependent on Pedro?

241
00:10:17.360 --> 00:10:19.640
-Aren't you almost broke yet?
-[doorbell buzzes]

